Grails validation capability is built on [Spring's Validator API|http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/javadoc-api/org/springframework/validation/package-summary.html] and data binding capabilities. However Grails takes this further and provides a unified way to define validation "constraints" with its constraints mechanism.

Constraints in Grails are a way to declaratively specify validation rules. Most commonly they are applied to [domain classes|guide:GORM], however [URL Mappings|guide:urlmappings] and [Command Objects|guide:commandObjects] also support constraints.
{hidden}

Capacidad de validación de Grails está construido sobre [la primavera Validator API|http://static.springsource.org/spring/docs/3.0.x/javadoc-api/org/springframework/validation/package-summary.html] y funciones de enlace de datos. Sin embargo Grails toma esto más y proporciona una forma unificada para definir la validación "restricciones" con su mecanismo de restricciones.Restricciones en Grails son una forma de especificar de forma declarativa las reglas de validación. Normalmente se aplican a [dominio classes|guide:GORM], sin embargo [URL Mappings|guide:urlmappings] y [comando Objects|guide:commandObjects] también son compatibles con las restricciones.
